Review.Titre: Every piece of seafood arrived thawed and warm!
Review.Contenu: So, I really tried to like this company.  They worked with me to get a discount code that worked and I thought it was going well. Though this may not be Fulton's error, it still left me with a box of worthless seafood.  Very disheartening, and a beware to anyone who lives any distance from the city. Not sure about their other products, but do NOT order lobster or scallops from this company.   Great miyagi oysters though.

Review.Contenu: We made our first order for my wifes 60th birthday. it took a week for them to even ship out and when they arrived the contents were NOT frozen and one container of scallops was crushed and ruined! Also we ordered 2 lobster tails and only recieved ONE!! I have reached out to tell you our problem thru your email and have not had anyone reach back to us to discuss the problem or offer some compensation!! We had heard good things of your company But...... as of this moment we are not very Impressed. Sincerely Jon

Review.Titre: You get the customer to the door with a…
Review.Contenu: You get the customer to the door with a nice promotional post card. Then, rather than exceed their expectations, you leave the customer relations at the door. When an order was placed, I received an email stating that they had run out of the variety of oysters requested. No problem I thought, I could substitute another variety and pay the difference. An email from customer service came back stating because I had checked the box "no substitutions" they couldn't do that. No thanks, I'll look elsewhere for my seafood.

Review.Titre: Food came a day late and unfrozen which…
Review.Contenu: Food came a day late and unfrozen which was meant to be for an important family dinner. We had to throw out the entire order and scramble to get a plan b. dinner  option.

Review.Titre: Frozen lobster tails arrived thawed
Review.Contenu: I ordered frozen lobster tails for Valentine's day.  The shipment was delayed and delivered 1 day plus 3 hours after the expected delivery.  The tails arrived thawed.  During a chat, I was told they could last up to 5 days in the refrigerator, which would take them to Valentine's day or I could partially cook and then refreeze them, which could cause a texture problem.  No thanks!  I don't care to take the chance of making me or my valentine sick.  I was also told if I chose to just refreeze them they may have bacteria as a result.  What a waste!

Review.Titre: I re ordered because first order was on…
Review.Contenu: I re ordered because first order was on the truck two days.  Today I received only part of my total order.  I cannot understand what is going on.  I have company right now and cannot enumerate all that is missing.  For one thing, there is no salmon at all in the order.  Help!

Review.Titre: The frozen salmon was defrosted by the…
Review.Contenu: The frozen salmon was defrosted by the time it arrived, the cherrystone clams were very large and too chewy (I threw them out), the mussels were stringy and had virtually no meat (I threw them out),  the littlenecks were OK but not as sweet when I get them at a raw bar. Very disappointed.

Review.Titre: I can't believe I paid 200 for a small…
Review.Contenu: I can't believe I paid 200 for a small bag of crablegs..the reason I bought it,because My coworker raved about the quantity of crablegs in a box and the price was the same,only she bought  her's in person ..I splurged and Im very disappointed, the bag of shrimp was also,A Joke..Never Again

Review.Titre: Fish was spoiled
Review.Contenu: Fish was delayed. It spent two days in an envelope with a small freezer pack.Needles to say it arrive, not cold and smelling. You did give us a full refund, but I would have much rather Ed enjoyed eating the fish.You should probably give it some thought about better packaging. I would be willing to pay extra for the cost of appropriate packaging, with possibly adding dry ice, for a cross country trip allowing for delays. (COVID, staffing etc.)I have to give it some thought if I will try to order again without information about better packaging.

Review.Titre: Not Fresh Tasting
Review.Contenu: Not Fresh TastingWe were not impressed by the packaging, nor the taste of these oysters. It was sad, because we were really looking forward to the illustrious product from the Fulton Fish Market. The oysters were in mesh bags, just like the inexpensive product at the grocery store.

Review.Titre: We had friends in town from the east…
Review.Contenu: We had friends in town from the east coast, I had ordered 4 dozen clams, which did not make it here until 3 days later. Very dissatisfied & your company didn’t offer any compensation! So next time I order fresh & timely seafood it will be from a different company

Review.Titre: I placed an order on 12/14 and sent a…
Review.Contenu: I placed an order on 12/14 and sent a notice that it would deliver on 12/16Checked on tracking and it was never sent. You charged my account and I have left several messages with no response. Very poor customer service. I would like a refund of my purchase, which was never shipped

Review.Titre: you deceived us by saying your stone crab…truly disappointed
Review.Contenu: you deceived us by saying your stone crabs were fresh when in fact they had been frozen. when they arrived, they smelled up the whole kitchen and they were slimy. we spent over 15 years spending time in Marathon Florida, we were friends with a crab fisherman, and he told us everything there was to know about crabs. the first was the worst thing you can do is freeze stone crab. we know what fresh crab smells and taste like. when we heard about Fulton fish market and how great you were we decided to try your stone crab for our anniversary, BAD CHOICE.needless to say, we will never order from you again.

Review.Titre: We were really excited about our order
Review.Contenu: We were really excited about our order. It arrived ontime and I followed all the instructions. I noticed that the an unusually strong smell upon opening the box but proceeded.  We were shucking and  on the second oyster, there was a little live crab inside.  As we continued, many of the oysters we shucked had a crab as well.  Some may consider this good luck or a delicacy but between that and the off-putting odor, we threw them all out.  I haved shucked oysters many times over the years but this was a first. Disappointing.

Review.Titre: Wasn't too impressed with quality and…
Review.Contenu: Wasn't too impressed with quality and size of the fish. Halibut was very dry. Scallops were just OK not fabulous. Trout are very thin. Could actually get better quality here in TN.

Review.Titre: What Happened to Free Shipping????
Review.Contenu: I have purchased from you since 2020 and the purchase I made last week contained a shipping charge of $19.  This is the first time it was included on my invoice; I've always enjoyed free shipping since all my orders are over $100.  I'd understand having a charge if the amount was less than $100 but over that should continue to receive free shipping.

Review.Titre: One of the bass was not properly…
Review.Contenu: One of the bass was not properly packed. 4 packs of bass, 1lb scallop. 1lb shrimp was over $100. I did pay lower price with promotion, but it was not worth of $100+

Review.Titre: package smelled fishy
Review.Contenu: package smelled fishy.  Salmon was packed 2 to a package but sizes were extremely different.  Didn't look anything like the photo when ordering.  Really disappointing.  Also was hoping for King Salmon from NZ but I received farmed salmon from Oregon.

Review.Titre: Ordered the Bluefin sushi kit 1
Review.Contenu: Ordered the Bluefin sushi kit 1Week in advance, but was not told it wasn’t available on day of shipping. Rest of Shipment arrived ok, (lobster tails and shrimp were great) but no note about the sushi kit. Poor communication! Had to wait in chat room for 15 minutes to get an explanation. Not sure I will order again.

Review.Titre: Disappointed
Review.Contenu: This is the second order we have received from Fultons. The first order was great, the lobster tails were huge and very tasty. This time, the tails are small 7-8oz. Not the 8-10oz we paid for and were expecting. For the price you charge for 8-10oz tails, you should get 8-10oz tails. I don’t think we will continue to buy seafood from you at the price you charge for such small portions. Smaller than advertised.

Review.Titre: Not wild salmon
Review.Contenu: Ordered wild sockeye salmon but what I received is not wild sockeye salmon.  Looked and tasted more like farm raised.

Review.Titre: Our order of periwinkles was replaced…
Review.Contenu: Our order of periwinkles was replaced with a bag of mussels. Very disappointing. We were not made aware of the change, and already bought mussels. Now we had way to many. If I had been aware of periwinkle’s not being available, I could have sourced them from somewhere else.

Review.Titre: Didn't Travel Well
Review.Contenu: Maybe because it traveled across the country, but the crab cakes were really soggy, even after cooking them longer.  The lobster tails were big, but not really a lot of flavor. Your service was outstanding though, sending it early because of the storm back east.

Review.Titre: Packaging for the frozen products is…
Review.Contenu: Packaging for the frozen products is awful. Fish placed widely apart on a sheet of cardboard not vacuumed sealed. Really unprofessional and very disappointing. Fish was good quality but regular prices are absurdly high. They should be better at vacuum sealing individual portions in thicker plastic to make it easier for customers who thaw day of in water.

Review.Titre: I ordered shrimp which were hard and…
Review.Contenu: I ordered shrimp which were hard and very smelly, oysters I ordered a dozen and two were open. Left a very bad fishy smell in my fridge. The only thing I liked was the frozen crab cakes. I didn’t have much trust in the shrimp. Texture was way off..

Review.Titre: shipment problems
Review.Contenu: The two lobsters I ordered at a relatively high price were in such bad shape that had to cook them immediately.  One of them was barely alive and would most likely be dead before the end of the day.you should ship sooner after receiving the order

Review.Titre: did not rec'd my order when it was due
Review.Contenu: did not rec'd my order when it was due.  got e-mail telling me when my order arrives throw away,  I could reorder or take a refund   THIS HAS NEVER HAPPEN BEFORE

Review.Titre: Honestly I expected more on the…
Review.Contenu: Honestly I expected more on the shipping part. Lobster tails were totally defrosted, the Caviar only had 11 days left to "best before date", and was also mushy and had no pop or flavor, other then salt. And the price of the ostera Caviar was way overpriced for old stock crap. Sorry

Review.Titre: This was a very disappointing…
Review.Contenu: This was a very disappointing experience. I ordered caviar and a dozen oysters to enjoy on New Years Day. We received caviar that expired before it was even shipped, and 2 of the oysters were off and inedible - this would have been apparent by inspection before packing by their color, texture and weight. I reached out to the company with photos and was immediately refunded for the caviar and prorated oysters. I subsequently asked for a refund of the $35 shipping and that was also processed without issue. I appreciate the customer service but I would have preferred fresh products. We planned a meal around the caviar and being that it was New Years Day, we could not secure a replacement.

Review.Titre: I ordered the FULTON'S FINEST ATLANTIC…
Review.Contenu: I ordered the FULTON'S FINEST ATLANTIC SALMON PORTIONS - 2CT Center Cut - Frozen because I thought it was not farm raised. It was farm raised.

Review.Titre: Fish has weird taste like farm raised…
Review.Contenu: Fish has weird taste like farm raised not wild caught fish and a smell of gas( petroleum)like they were caught closed to boats.Delivery and handling was exceptional.I love the packaging just the fish taste weird.

Review.Titre: My shellfish was filthy, small, difficult to open, and tasteless
Review.Contenu: While the offer I purchased my 2 dozen oysters from was amazing, (up to $50, pay shipping only), my oysters weren't.I've shucked & eaten oysters my entire life, growing up in Florida.The oysters I received from Fulton were filthy.  Seriously dirty. muddy, and it took a scouring pad scrubbing & 2 toothbrushes to remove the dirt.They were also very small.I did have a single bad one in each bag...They were also extremely difficult to open.Had to steam practically half of them due to the fact the shells were very brittle and broke when I tried getting my oyster knife under the valve part to pry.I was expecting a nice fresh, salty taste to the oysters as well, but they were tasteless.I had to add salt & seasonings to every single one to "taste" them.I am happy I didn't pay full price for these, and I won't be ordering any more from Fulton, either.

Review.Titre: I had a $100 off an order of $150 with…
Review.Contenu: I had a $100 off an order of $150 with free shipping. I spent $160 and since I love all types of fish and had free shipping I know I asked for substitutions. I only got half of what I ordered and was told I opted out of substitutions (no I did not). While the fish I got seemed fresh, I am still upset that I only got half my order. Seems to me the “ great deal” was just a scam. Spend a lot to take advantage of a great deal but it’s not a deal. I could have been a repeat customer but not now.

Review.Titre: My scallops and tuna were thawed
Review.Contenu: My scallops and tuna were thawed, the other fish were all frozen still though. Perhaps faulty packaging?

Review.Titre: The food is perfectly fine...if not…
Review.Contenu: The food is perfectly fine...if not just a bit over priced. However, the food is delivered by FEDEX, who will leave the food , unsigned for, in the lobby of my NYC apartment building. Not interested in this service anymore

Review.Titre: A False Balance
Review.Contenu: In this digital age it is easy for a good name to get a bad name. I have always suspected that I am being short changed with the weigh of your fish. My last delivery, I decided to weigh a few of the fish and it was worst than I thought. For example, your small porgy 14.5 oz, 12.4 oz (card board packing removed). Porgy 1.1.2 lb and 14.5 oz (with card board packing). Your 2.5 lb. salmon  bone, head & tail was 1.12.8 lb.  Fish are sold by lbs. not by cut. The weight posted on the website and on the label must correspond with the weight.

Review.Titre: The red snapper and the smoked salmon…
Review.Contenu: The red snapper and the smoked salmon were good, but the oysters and the monk fish all waisted, the box was warm, the dry ice melted

Review.Titre: Limited choices and my choice has been…
Review.Contenu: Limited choices and my choice has been substituted even though I specified not to substitute.

Review.Titre: All frozen items were thawed and barely…
Review.Contenu: All frozen items were thawed and barely cool.Change of packaging since I last received was not sufficient

Review.Titre: one of my items was missing from the…
Review.Contenu: one of my items was missing from the order. other than that, quality service and products.

Review.Titre: Still waiting for my delivery
Review.Contenu: Still waiting for my delivery - frustrating you don’t know I haven’t received my order and you are sending me a survey?

Review.Titre: Disappointing oyster quality
Review.Contenu: Ordered a dozen oysters but only received 8, 3 of which were either inedible or empty. The rest of the order was fine.

Review.Titre: I ordered 3 snow crab legs (1 cluster /…
Review.Contenu: I ordered 3 snow crab legs (1 cluster / each) and 1 king crab legs (2 legs) . The snow crab legs taste ok. The king crab legs does not taste good and too small. The legs are too small and broken when I received them even though the package was good and secured. I would not buy this again for this quality of the product. The king crab legs are as small as the snow crab legs.

Review.Titre: Packaging wasn't good as products…
Review.Contenu: Packaging wasn't good as products arrived melted and many of the products were drenched, causing them to be open.

Review.Titre: I am not feeling well and have been…
Review.Contenu: I am not feeling well and have been throwing up since I ate the fish. Not sure if I did something wrong or was wrong with fish

Review.Titre: About a dozen were broken
Review.Contenu: About a dozen were broken. Also, half or so we're not little neck clams. I selected no substitutions and still got some top and middle necks.

Review.Titre: The fish was excellent and arrived as…
Review.Contenu: The fish was excellent and arrived as promised.  The problem:  Preparation instructions were not followed.  I asked for the fish to be filleted and skinned.  They were not.  When I started using Fulton two years ago, the requests were honored.  Last year they were partially honored.  This year not at all.  Full disclosure this year I was warned that Fulton had no control over requests.  Apparently they don't anymore.  Time to find another fish monger.

Review.Titre: This farmed pompano from Indonesia.
Review.Contenu: This farmed pompano from Indonesia is no where near as good as wild caught pompano and is definitely not worth the price I paid.  My guests were not impressed in the least. Very disappointing.  Won't be ordering again.

Review.Titre: My order arrived a day late
Review.Contenu: My order arrived a day late, which destroyed my anniversary dinner. I would suggest ordering only if there is not a time sensitive issue

Review.Titre: The quality was disappointing…
Review.Contenu: The quality was disappointing especially the oysters. Some are rotten.  Awful

Review.Titre: Fish weights less than advertised
Review.Contenu: We have used this company before and the quality and service was great. I was planning to do nice dinner for my family and needed jumbo size fish.  On 09/23/2022 I bought 2 whole White fish and one jumbo branzino. White fish was advertised as 2-3 lb. per fish but came both weighted 1.8 lb. per fish.  Branzino was advertised to weight 1.75 to 2.25 lb. but came only 0.8lb. I called customer service and  explained lady that I don't need tiny fish but she could only return half the price for the brazino. But I needed jumbo fish for my recipe. It ruined my dinner. I had to go Whole Food and buy another one.

Review.Titre: I wanted to try East Coast clams
Review.Contenu: I wanted to try East Coast clams.  Had no idea they would be so filthy.  I've been spoiled by WA.

Review.Titre: Everything was thawed
Review.Contenu: Everything was thawed. I guess you can't get frozen to Tx.

Review.Titre: Ordered oysters and clams
Review.Contenu: Ordered oysters and clams. I live in Florida. The Beau Soleil we ordered were spot-on and as great as ever. The Duxbury XL were lacking in quality and some of the top neck clams were warm upon opening the package and noticeably comprised. I should add the packaging was great, but perhaps the trip to Florida may have been too much for the delivery. Remember, "it's never as good as when you're there."

Review.Titre: Horrible experience
Review.Contenu: Overnight shipping turned into 2 night shipping very late in the evening with an opened box and several pounds of thawed bluefish shoved into a box too small to contain the amount of fish I ordered. I called and asked for a refund and Maria was understanding and very apologetic and resolved the issue fairly quickly but I am highly upset about the way this turned out overall. My brother recommended this company to me and speaks highly of the bluefish there but was shocked about what happened with my order. He said “That doesn’t sound like Fulton Fish Market at all.” I’d like to place another one day soon but afraid that I may receive the same service.

Review.Titre: I ordered to be delivered on the 31st…
Review.Contenu: I ordered to be delivered on the 31st and instead it was shipped already

Review.Titre: I ordered a WHOLE side of salmon and…
Review.Contenu: I ordered a WHOLE side of salmon and received pieces. If I wanted pieces I would have ordered individual filets. It was for a dinner party and had to scratch making the salmon

Review.Titre: All of the Smelt that were deliver to…
Review.Contenu: All of the Smelt that were deliver to me were all freezer burnt. I could send pictures if I knew how to do that.  Fish sticks were extremely good. Probably the best I've ever had.

Review.Titre: Uni is not very fresh..
Review.Contenu: Uni is not very fresh... not as sweet as expected, considering the price. It has some sands or sea urchin's shell in it. very disappointed...[Update] the customer service is very kind and patient. I forgot to mention last time that the packaging is super nice as there's no leakage. Appreciate all these. I would still order from Fulton

Review.Titre: Love the products!!
Review.Contenu: Love the products!!Everything came completely thawed! Refrozen as per your information Lots of dry ice but it wasn’t even near the product Will be eating crab cakes tonight and lobster hopefully no problem will occur

Review.Titre: Poorly filleted shad
Review.Contenu: Poorly filleted shadI included in my order 3 shad filets based on the claim of how good their people were that the filets would be bone free.This was not the case!! There were so many bones in each bite that I was afraid of getting some stuck in my throat.I threw that filet away and will not eat the others.Trust in my fishmonger is very important and they let me down.Thank you

Review.Titre: Poor Performance - Shad Partially deboned Filets and Smashed Roe
Review.Contenu: Fish/Roe were fresh and tasty. Shipping was satisfactory. Packaging was poor. The Roe was put on the bottom and was smashed and one of the rose sets was completely separated into pieces. The listed product as "deboned Filets" were a complete inacuracy. The four filets were only partially deboned and it took over 30min and the loss of large pieces of meat to properly remove major 3" bones and minor "pin bones". This so called deboning was done by amateurs not professionals that understand how to debone a boney fish called Shad!

Review.Titre: Disappointed.
Review.Contenu: My delivery was way later than expected. The fish/shrimp were partially unfrozen and smelly. The shrimp’s texture had no snap, it was mushy. Yuck. I spent a pretty penny to treat myself and family bc I survived CoVid. I only had 3% chance of living, I was on a ventilator for a long time and almost died twice! So the seafood was my welcome home dinner treat after almost a month in icu. I’m very disappointed bc I grew up in NYC.

Review.Titre: the fish was excellent. but the packaging wasn't.
Review.Contenu: the fish was excellent... However the way in which it was packaged allowed all the fish to arrive warm( the frozen shrimp were thawed). The shipper did there job so it must be the packaging of the fish.  If the fish would have arrived in a frozen and cold state my review would of been 5 stars.

Review.Titre: Delivery was fine -But!
Review.Contenu: Delivery was fine, and on time.The oysters were about half dried up, with no or little juice in them.Perhaps it was because they shipped them from the west coast to the east coast, and back again to the west coast. To California , where we live.Contrary to what I was told by your representative when I asked about it.She said. " Of course they would be shipped directly from the west coast sources."

Review.Titre: When the package arrived it was partly…
Review.Contenu: When the package arrived it was partly thawed and the fish were not frozen as originally suggested. Some of the packaging released fishy odor, however packaging was not open. I thought you would’ve sent it by a insulated carton instead of paper carton with plastic encased with ice packs and brown paper. I was not impressed with your service, even though it was a small package I felt like it was not being handled in an appropriate way. I will not be ordering from your organization again and will let other people know not to order as well.

Review.Titre: FedEx Delay
Review.Contenu: I know a FedEx delay is not the fault of the Fish Market, but when the delivery misses the date of a dinner party, it is a problem. Maybe the answer is to have it delivered a day before you need it. Not sure, but will think twice about ordering for a specific event. I froze the fish and will give it a try in the next few weeks.

Review.Titre: No refund back to my card for out of stock items
Review.Contenu: One item is out of stock. I've waited for almost a month and no refund is back to my card. I have to reach out to customer service to get my money back. If I didn't check my bank statement, I would have missed it.Frozen items arrived completely thawed. I have never experienced this with other meat and seafood websites.

Review.Titre: Poor shipping quality, small tails.
Review.Contenu: Took over a week to get the order to ship, but it was around the holidays so I can understand that but we had to source our NY meal at a local shop which ended up getting us much nicer lobster tails anyways.Box showed up sort of wet, all the lobster were no longer frozen, the bag they were in was not sealed and the tails were small. Had to refreeze them all because I had just finished cooking the tails we locally sourced.Don't think I'd use Fulton again.

Review.Titre: My first order was fresh fish not…
Review.Contenu: My first order was fresh fish not frozen , no fish smell and amazing and packaged perfect. Now I received frozen fish , opened the boxed and got hit with a powerful stink of fish. Salmon pieces were not the same at all and slimmy. It was horrible a lot went in the garbage. I will never order again, and all my friends I told to , I will tell them never again

Review.Titre: Not Worth the Trouble
Review.Contenu: Very dissapointed in the product and service.  An item was not shipped and i was advised prior to shipping it would not be available.  It took an additional 2 emails to request credit.  The packaging wreaked of old fish and I will not be ordering again.  I’m ordering fish, all the boxes, ice and packaging doesn’t have to smell like oldFish

Review.Titre: We got 2 dozens oysters and 2# of crab…
Review.Contenu: We got 2 dozens oysters and 2# of crab legs. The oysters were decent but the crab was disappointing. One of the large legs that was 6 inches long had only 1 inch of meat in it, the other was fine. Considering the legs were 89 bucks it was disappointing. I have not had this happen from other places I have ordered from.

Review.Titre: I ordered my fish a month before…
Review.Contenu: I ordered my fish a month before Thanksgiving requesting a delivery the day before & planning my family meal around it. My fish didn’t arrive until the afternoon the day after Thanksgiving despite it having been shipped on the Tuesday before. I emailed customer service & am still waiting to hear back. I won’t order from them again. 😢Update: I heard back & was issued a refund. I do realize this was partly a FedEx issue.

Review.Titre: Not worth $ throw together, half thawed
Review.Contenu: Scallops wrapped with bacon in two thin crushed boxes you get at the supermarket. Bags of lobster tails loose and half thawed and we opened it upon arrival.the oysters sane thing. Thrown in a muck, loose in unsealed bags. Not worth the money and definitely will not order again. Worried to use tomorrow for Christmas, to be honest.

Review.Titre: Very Small fish and not as shown on Website..
Review.Contenu: Fishes were very Small, as not even halt the size as shown in Pictures. Pictures showed the Cleaned large fish ( without head ) but arrived as small full body fish. Very disappointed and will not recommend or buy again..   My local Asian stores sell much cheaper and way larger fish Besides that shipping / packaging was good.

Review.Titre: Hungry again and left down.
Review.Contenu: Good fish when it shows up. We have ordered multiple times that the fish never showed up as promised and when it does it had to be disposed of by us or the carrier service. We had to make multiple trips to our local store for destroyed meal plans with family waiting with money spent on thinking the fish would be our meal and not so. I write this as no fish for our meal again two days later.

Review.Titre: Poor shipping
Review.Contenu: I placed 3 orders with you since just before the holidays,  The first order came late, the second order you cancelled due to logistics problems, and this last order the fish came fine but the Lobster Tails were completely defrosted and unusable.  Not a very good way to start off with a new customer.

Review.Titre: I order your products because of the individual orders
Review.Contenu: I order your products because of the individual wrap capable. I spefically asked that my order was to be wrapped in a specific way on the order and then I followed up with a phone call to confirm my special notes..All of that was in vein..It came all bulk wrapped so then it had to be separated and wrapped again. 2nd time this happened... Very disappointing.

Review.Titre: Bad service
Review.Contenu: I was told my order would be delivered Tuesday and it wasnt delivered until Wednesday. Mostly thawed.  Your customer service email said I should eat it now basically. That's a lot of money to force yourself to eat before you are ready.  Disappointed.  Thought I found a place to get seafood.  Wont do it again

Review.Titre: The Jonah crab claws were very small
Review.Contenu: The Jonah crab claws were very small.  Fed ex was to bring them between 9:30 and 2 :pm  They did show up until 8PM. Because of the size they were too much work for the amount of meat.   They also came in pcs. not all whole.Smoked salmon was fine.  But will not reorder claws from you again.

Review.Titre: I live alone and all of my order was thawed on arrival.
Review.Contenu: I live alone and all of my order arrived thawed.I had no choice but to freeze it anyway I have no idea if it will still be enjoyable when I defrost it. I have ordered meat and seafood online before and they use dry ice in my product and it was delivered frozen. So I am disappointed. What I have had so far been great.

Review.Titre: I ordered to large 3 pound lobsters
Review.Contenu: I ordered to large 3 pound lobsters .  The shipping info was dated 12AM Monday morning to be arriving Tuesday.  That means it was sitting in the box for a day and half by the time the arrived.  They were loosely wrapped I in moist paper. The lobster was very very dry when they arrived at my house Tuesday at 4:00 PM.  I was not happy with the quality of those lobsters .

Review.Titre: I ordered fresh (never frozen)…
Review.Contenu: I ordered fresh (never frozen) untreated scallops for the second time.  The first delivery was everything I could hope (and was paying) for.  They shed virtually no moisture so they browned on the outside while the inside was still moist and pure tasting.  Wonderful!This delivery looked good but shed a terrific amount of moisture as it cooked, not a fleck of browning possible tho exact same preparation.  What the heck happened?!  NOT a happy thing to serve to dinner party guests.

Review.Titre: The website did not work when I tried…
Review.Contenu: The website did not work when I tried to checkout with two gift cards for Father’s Day. I had to wait until the following Monday after the holiday to order my gifts. I never received a confirmation email and the gift cards were not sent to my recipients until I text messaged a customer service rep on Tuesday. I do not have a lot of confidence in placing future orders with Fulton and would not recommend.

Review.Titre: Didn’t have what I ordered in stock so…
Review.Contenu: Didn’t have what I ordered in stock so instead of asking me for a replacement or order cancelation, they sent the in stock items which was one snow crab cluster, which was underweight and broken into multiple pieces. Contacted customer service and offered a 20% coupon on next purchase. No attempt to fix existing order issues

Review.Titre: Disappointed
Review.Contenu: I ordered a bundle and 4 portions of monk fish. The box came with the monk fish only, that wasn’t frozen. I had planned a special meal with my wife, and this was disappointing to say the least. I did receive a credit but I feel I wasted my first time purchase discount and free shipping on 4 portions of fish. I’m glad we placed a single order before a subscription service, now we know not to. We have had a subscription with Butcher Box for several years, we were hoping your products would complement theirs. Unfortunately it doesn’t appear so.I hope this feedback is helpful!

Review.Titre: Terrible Shipping
Review.Contenu: So I wasn't able to try fish from Fulton Fish Market. I ordered twice and both times it was held up by FedEx so the shipment came late. Which meant we received bad fish twice. The second time Fulton Fish Market was trying to correct the first mistake. I did get my money back, but was disappointed that this happened twice.

Review.Titre: Disappointing
Review.Contenu: I ordered scallops and sea urchin. The u-10 scallops were fishy and had no flavor, they were bland and had no sweetness. The uni was also pretty mediocre.The customer service was on point and refunded me immediately but the food ordered was extremely disappointing.

Review.Titre: Hoping to give a better review next time…if I ever get to try the product.
Review.Contenu: Hoping to give a better review next time, but for now I have to give this this very few stars. .My first order and the delivery completely failed. Was told to throw out whatever comes (if it comes), and was given an option to reorder or have a refund.  So on the service side, I give them a few stars, but on the actual delivery side no stars so far.

Review.Titre: Not the weight you paid for…
Review.Contenu: Fulton has experimented over the decades with different packaging for steamer clams. These clams are very soft shelled clams that break easy. Currently, the packaging methods is much worse than the previous method. You are guaranteed to have about a 10% loss due to crushed clams. In addition, you can also expect about another 10% less weight overall from Fulton. I’ve been ordering from Fulton a long time and have never been shipped the full weight I paid for. It’s just expected now.

Review.Titre: I am disappointed with my experience
Review.Contenu: I am disappointed with my experience. My order was shorted with smaller portion sizes than what I ordered. A  substitution was made giving me all the same kind of fish (fresh and frozen) and the entire order, including the frozen portions were delivered at nearly room temperature. I was given a credit of $3. rather than Fulton fish  correcting my order and sending out the 2 correct portion sizes that were shorted.The fish we prepared so far was good but not worth the price and hassle for this family

Review.Titre: Scheduled our dinner party for Friday…
Review.Contenu: Scheduled our dinner party for Friday night. Received the package on time and in good shape.  Ordered Prime soft shell crabs for $34.99 to serve for dinner.  We were told that the Primes were unavailable and the Jumbo soft shells would be substituted, which would be fine.  When we opened our package to our disappointment there were NO soft shells.  So we cancelled our dinner party.  Not a good first time Fulton experience.

Review.Titre: Fish not labeled
Review.Contenu: First of all the fish was great. We had a $500 order of 32 pieces of fish, cod and halibut. None of it was labeled! The labels were all attached to one another and sitting on top of the stack of fish. So no we play "guess what this is" every time we eat the fish. I sent an email and the response was for me to send a picture of all of the packages. They made a huge mistake yet wanted me to go to my deep freeze and do all that work. No follow up. No future discount.

Review.Titre: Did an order for the wife’s birthday…
Review.Contenu: Did an order for the wife’s birthday who wanted an bunch of oysters. We did four dozen. The oysters we’re fresh but almost every payer was spawning. The texture was very unpleasant. Order arrived on time. Also did some Gin and Tonic salmon which was hard to get the G&T notes. Nothing was terrible, just not a great

Review.Titre: I would of given 5 stars except that…
Review.Contenu: I would of given 5 stars except that the kumomotto oysters were very bad quality! Most of them when opened was completely dryed out. Out of 2 dozen there were only 13 that could be used and even the 13 that were used. They didn't taste like real kumomotto and they were all inedible and we just throw them away. They were the most expensive and not usable.  Also I thought the state of Texas wasn't allowed to have kumomotto so I am concerned what oysters were given to me.  But all the other oysters and clams were amazing.

Review.Titre: The fish I bought was too small for the…
Review.Contenu: The fish I bought was too small for the money.You should’ve thrown the fish back and let them grow to a nice size. Your selection is very limited and I’ll take my chances in search the local fish market.

Review.Titre: King Crab Legs and Butterfish
Review.Contenu: We ordered the king crab legs and butterfish for 2-day delivery.  When we received the order and opened the box, we immediately smelled bad fish.  Most of the butterfish was thrown away.  Some of the crab legs were dry and others moist. Very disappointed as our previous order of Branzino and clams were great.

Review.Titre: Almost got it right
Review.Contenu: Got the order A-day after it was supposed to be here.. It was missing one item and I was told in an email that someone would get back to me about it. So far that has not happened. Other than that the nap the seafood is fresh it arrived cold , and is everything I expected.

Review.Titre: I specifically set up my profile to not…
Review.Contenu: I specifically set up my profile to not allow substitutions.  Yet, two out of three items were in fact substituted, including the Dover Sole, which was the specific reason i placed my order in the first place.  Upon prompt arrival, the frozen Black Cod I’d ordered arrived completely defrosted.  I don’t see this as the end of the world, but I’ve ordered frozen, individually portioned steaks via mail order and had no problems with them arriving fully frozen.Finally, your website describes the portion as a filet.  I’d love more specificity in terms of general weight or how many portions that includes.

Review.Titre: My wife became very ill with 12 hours…
Review.Contenu: My wife became very ill with 12 hours of vomiting to the point that she passed out on her way from bathroom to bed.Likely Staphylococcal in origin.  Had uni and anchovies (from Spain).  have enjoyed the meals that worked, and your team is great, but won't risk that again.

Review.Titre: Packaging Problem
Review.Contenu: I want to order fresh, authentic wild caught seafood to fit into my new diet change program.  Your web site said impressive things, and I decided to give you a try with your new promotion.  Your response time was excellent; you kept your delivery promise; however, the package that arrived on time was not effectively packaged that all the Frozen order arrived completely thawed - big disappointment.  Inspecting the quality of food, they look fresh from their thawed state; but I just can't consume all these food in time when they were all thawed at the same time.

Review.Titre: A disappointing dinner party courtesy FedEx
Review.Contenu: We scheduled a dinner party featuring soft shell crab, which is quite an exotic dish for rural Eastern Oregon.  Fulton did their part and the soft shell crab and other goodies for the party left New York as scheduled.  Unfortunately, FedEx let us all down and the package will arrive on day late, the seafood spoiled.These are difficult times and we realize the express companies are having a tough time keeping up with demand.  Fulton did fully refund our purchase but our guests were disappointed that soft shell crab will not make it onto the menu tonight.

Review.Titre: The delivery was pretty fast and I…
Review.Contenu: The delivery was pretty fast and I believe the product was delivered as it was intended to be. But the smoked whitefish you are selling is so salty that I can't eat it. I know you don't make it you just sell it. But you need to sell a good product.

Review.Titre: Incomplete order
Review.Contenu: Incomplete order.  My variety of pack of salmon, coho and halibut did not contain halibut.  I received cod instead despite my checking no substitutions.  Waiting to see if company remedies the situation before deciding if I will order again from them.

Review.Titre: What a Mess!
Review.Contenu: One should NEVER put the mesh bag of Oysters on top of all the fish order UNLESS you properly cleans the Oysters so that dirt and shell do not end up all over the order.   Swordfish as a replacement for TUNA is probably not equal unless one was to give more Swordfish and/or replace it with something else.  The scallops were not fresh but partially frozen and thawing en route.  This make them impossible to fry properly as the moisture was still in the Scallops.   I was so hoping that this would be special and become a regular order for me but way too much waste in packaging and delivery to be sustainable for me or the environment.

Review.Titre: Never got here as they claimed weather…
Review.Contenu: Never got here as they claimed weather conditions issues

Review.Titre: Very Disappointed!!
Review.Contenu: I am very disappointed with this delivery.  I have ordered before and was quite satisfied.  First the box was left outside the lobby of my. Apartment house with out at least letting me know it was there. I realize this was a  Fed Ex problem.When I was notified by the office that a package was left for me it was hours after the delivery.  Upon opening the box there was an awful Oder and I discovered the package where the soft shell crabs were to be contained was split open and the packing had crushed at least half of the crabs.

Review.Titre: Have not tried the swordfish yet but it…
Review.Contenu: Have not tried the swordfish yet but it looks pretty nice.  The reason for the two stars was the mussels.  About 1/4 of them were open and dead and had to throw them away.  There was still ice in the box so it they didn't go bad for lack of refrigeration.

Review.Titre: Great Food, Poor Availability and Communication
Review.Contenu: The seafood I received was great. However, most of my order ended up being out of stock and therefore was not shipped. The emails telling me my seafood was on the way did not alert me to this, and showed the full order as on its way along with the full amount that was charged to my credit card. I was really disappointed upon opening my box and finding most of what I ordered missing. When I checked my order history online, I saw that a credit was processed for the missing portion of my order (which I am waiting to post to my credit card).What was shipped was received extremely fresh and was of excellent quality.

Review.Titre: Displeased With Substitution In My Order
Review.Contenu: I ordered Porgy filets, and because they didn't have the size in ounces that I ordered, I received an email stating that it was replaced with a smaller ounce filet. When I received the order, instead of the 4 filets, there were 4 whole Porgies with the head and tails on. I am partially disabled, and it was very difficult to cut the heads and tails off, and clean the insides out. Also, there were many scales left on the fish. The reason I always order filets is because they are easier for me to handle. I am very disappointed with the order, and it makes me skeptical about ordering from Fulton Fish Market again.

Review.Titre: Good fish, poorly cut.
Review.Contenu: We decided to order salmon filets, for our first time, from New York Fulton Fish Market. The salmon picture advertising this company in the New York Times cooking section looked wonderful. The fish was shipped quickly and arrived in New Mexico in record time. The salmon is quite good, but the filets are cut any old way, some nice and thick, others flat and larger. Not two are alike (even though the weights are probably all the same). So, the fish does not look at all like the advertisement. It would be nice to have all 16 portions, center cut, similar sizes, thickness and shape. It would make it easier to cook and much more appetizing.

Review.Titre: Bad first experience
Review.Contenu: The first order of 10 lobsters arrived after 3 days and was completely defrosted. The outside box smelled of fish and the bottom of the box was soaked.  We were told to discard this order . We reordered 10 more  thinking this was probably a fluke. We did receive the second order today after 2 days. Although the ice was intact, the foam top was all caved in and the lobster was completely thawed. I think that Fulton Fisk market needs to upgrade their packing materials especially during these hot summer days. This was our first order. Not a good experience as this lobster is not cheap.

Review.Titre: I reached out when my shipment was late…
Review.Contenu: I reached out when my shipment was late (Fed Ex) and the seafood was mostly thawed, rendering it useless for a dinner party several days later. The concern was received by Fulton but no resolution was offered.  Poor customer service.

Review.Titre: The portion sizes small for the cost so…
Review.Contenu: The portion sizes small for the cost so i do not see the value in ordering from you direct.  Sams Club has better quality and better prices.

Review.Titre: Ordered some frozen - everythings was defrosted
Review.Contenu: The normal place I purchase from packs everything in dry ice.  Fulton Fish Market packs everything with frozen blocks of ice.  I ordered 2 items that were suppose to be frozen and 2 items (not available as frozen) fresh and everything that showed up was defrostedWe are normally buying to store in our freezer NOT sure if I would every order again - especially in the summer.  I think there packing system needs a lot of work.

Review.Titre: Marketing degree from a box of cheerios.
Review.Contenu: I didn't receive a personal greeting, no card for who packed my order. When I placed the order it asked if I wanted a personal message on the order. That didn't happen. I also did not need advertisement card in my package. Another thing... iv been a customer for a couple years now. Seeing that I can receive extra savings suddenly if I become a member is insulting since iv ordered many times before. The process has gone from smooth to annoying.

Review.Titre: Crab meat …
Review.Contenu: Last year’s crab meat order was delicious. This year’s crab meat order was not so good,  smelled very fishy and did not taste like blue claw crab meat. I reached out to customer service and they gave me a full refund so I am changing my review as their customer service is outstanding .

Review.Titre: Fresh but concerned about packaging
Review.Contenu: Overall the fish looks/smells very fresh.  I am concerned with the packaging.  The fish was very well packed with plenty of ice bags but the fish did seem warmer than I expected.  I freeze it immediately after receiving it.  Hopefully the fish will be fine when I get ready to cook it

Review.Titre: Overall experience with Fulton has been…
Review.Contenu: Overall experience with Fulton has been great in the past.  The reason for only 3 star is because my order is split into two shipments with one part from California. It was supposed to be delivered on the Xmas eve, but still showing delayed status today after Xmas. I know it is Xmas holiday and there are not a lot people working. It is understandable the order is late. Hopefully this is handled well either I get a refund or a replacement shipment will be on the way. We will see. It is a day after xmas. No one has responded yet as Fulton is closed.

Review.Titre: Would order again...
Review.Contenu: The delivery was perfectly handled. While the Beau Soleil and the Royal Miyagi oysters were in good condition, the Kumamotos had no "liquor" remaining once opened - almost completely dry. Not sure why but it made them difficult to enjoy (and they are my favorite). I don't blame Fulton Fish as this happens from time to time.

Review.Titre: I ordered frozen lobster tails and…
Review.Contenu: I ordered frozen lobster tails and shrimp, plus some non-frozen items.  I was aware that, because it was a mix of frozen and non-frozen, cold packs would be used instead of dry ice.  But even with overnight shipping the lobster tails and shrimp arrived defrosted which meant I had to use both within a couple of days as it is unsafe to refreeze shellfish.  The quality of the lobster  and shrimp was excellent, however.  I've ordered many frozen food items that were shipped with cold packs and did not defrost during shipping.

Review.Titre: I ordered 16 porgy fillets for a family…
Review.Contenu: I ordered 16 porgy fillets for a family reunion.  I was under the impression the fish would be gutted and scaled.  I was dismayed to see the level of scales that remained on the fish.  Paying $175 for an order that was not completely fulfilled is disheartening :(

Review.Titre: Only repeat ONLY ONE order was given…
Review.Contenu: Only repeat ONLY ONE order was given before 12/25 now the recipient has received TWO more since that date. Wil never repeat NEVER reccomend Fulton  to ANYBODY!! We are now $276.00 in debt!! How do you explain this?? Hell of a way to do business!!

Review.Titre: Upside/downside
Review.Contenu: The downside: the order of fish received (mahi mahi) wasn’t at all the excellent quality we’d gotten in the past—had large portions of bloodline, which we don’t eat. The upside: the customer service was amazing, and very gracious. We’ll come back and try again.

Review.Titre: Whiting Online Fish Order
Review.Contenu: My order arrived on December 28, 2022.  I received the order directly from the Fedex delivery person.  After immediately opening the box it was determined that the fish was completed thawed out and nothing inside was cold.  In an effort to hopefully save the fish it was placed in the freezer.  Due to the the coolder weather in my area hopefully the whiting fish will not spoil before it is eaten.  I have no explanation why the fish was not frozen or cold  when it was received, however it was noticed that one of the bottom flaps on the box was not secure.  I cooked four pieces of the fish December 30, 2022 and it appeared to be ok.

Review.Titre: Packaging could look better
Review.Contenu: I think the vacuum package could be better, smaller; flesh laid out better. As is product looks carelessly sealed. Website hard to navigate; menu could be labeled by fish type: fish, shell fish, sauces, etc. instead of just pages to click.  Delivery dates hard to change or edit.

Review.Titre: Bait switch for all..
Review.Contenu: The quality of the products I have received has been wonderful.. The only issue for me is that many times I will place an order based on sp0ecials, discounts etc. I do generally buy other items as well. The problem is that when it is time to ship items that have already been paid for. It seems that often times it is the special or discounted item becomes unavailable. In many cases I only went to the site for those items..

Review.Titre: Delivery
Review.Contenu: Product was never delivered. Fed Ex problem not FF. FF handled the problem immediately and issued full credit in minutes. Very professional but disappointed we never got the product. Will try again another time.

Review.Titre: Fish was not delivered overnight
Review.Contenu: Fish was not delivered overnight. Sat somewhere and was room temperature when arrived.Thank you for your quick customer reply and remedy.  I will look for the full refund from my bank card.

Review.Titre: One of two Lobster Died
Review.Contenu: Delivery came with 6 packs of leaking ice gel blocks. Ordered two lobsters with each in their own box. One of the Lobsters came dead on arrival. Box was way too big and too heavy for two lobsters.

Review.Titre: Coho a no show!
Review.Contenu: The order was for coho and sockeye filets and no coho was sent.  They are out of stock but didnt notify me or give me the chance to change ny order.  Not the best first impression.

Review.Titre: "Jumbo" scallops very disappointing
Review.Contenu: "Jumbo" scallops were tiny bay scallops; the bacon was off the skewers and floating around the box. The Littleneck clams were fine. Saving the caviar for Christmas and hoping it will be savory.

Review.Titre: Fish quality aren’t good
Review.Contenu: Fish quality aren’t good. Looks like low grade fish. King salmon quality looks like Atlantic salmon. Origin is not clear stated. Packing is excellent.

Review.Titre: just a little bit disappointed
Review.Contenu: i was disappointed in that i was expecting colossal shrimp and received x-large sized shrimp . other then that the product was excellent

Review.Titre: I got a gift to use at the Fulton…
Review.Contenu: I got a gift to use at the Fulton Street Fish Market, so I decided to try it. I ordered scallops & crab legs. They were wrapped beautifully, in a fully insulated box. They let me know when it was arriving, too.I cooked the seafood thay night & the scallops were fresh, tender & delicious. However, the crab legs were inedible because of extreme salt! My husband gave up on them, & threw them out after eating only 1 leg. We were both extremely disappointed. I got the scallops for me & the crab for him, but we had to share the scallops, & it wasn't a large enough portion for 2 of us. We realize that these are creatures coming from the (salty) ocean, but we've had delicious crab legs before thst weren't this salty.I don't think we'll order from them again. The big expense is not worth it. Sorry.

Review.Titre: The fish was all defrosted  upon arrirval.Omaha Steak sends their fish completely frozen.
Review.Contenu: The fish was all defrosted  upon arrival. Omaha Steak sends its products frozen. Also their fish.   I received it Tuesday, Feb.14, 2023. Please revise  'your date of experience' format. It is difficult to use the way   the way you wish the event happened.

Review.Titre: I love the fresh fish and the…
Review.Contenu: I love the fresh fish and the selections to choose from. The only thing that I don't like is that I have to spend a minimum of $75 in order to get what I want. I live on a fixed income and cannot always afford to do this. You are the only ones I can get rainbow trout from. I absolutely love trout. It brings back memories. I would order more if I did not have to buy that amount.

Review.Titre: Good but…
Review.Contenu: I really did enjoy the quality of the oysters and fish but very disappointed with the mussels.  I had to throw all of them all away due to a majority of them being cracked.

Review.Titre: the Uni is so Disappointing
Review.Contenu: the Uni is so Disappointing！It's expensive, but it doesn't feel very fresh to eat，Because it doesn't really can taste anything . Not worth it at all! but the oyster is good.

Review.Titre: seafood tower overpriced
Review.Contenu: 12 of the oysters were not eatable for one and for the price I have gotten much better value ordering seperate items. I just was not impressed at all with this.Sorry!

Review.Titre: The Duxbury oysters were just too…
Review.Contenu: The Duxbury oysters were just too large, only got one open without baking.  Some of the shells were also very wormy.But the taste was excellent, especially the raw one.The salmon roe was fine, as last time.

Review.Titre: Huge price increases!
Review.Contenu: Prices have skyrocketed over the last year. Selection is way slim as well. Searching for other places to buy seafood online.

Review.Titre: Oysters in 2022
Review.Contenu: Delivery was prompt and product arrived in good condition. The quality of the oysters, especially the Blue Points, was mediocre at best.

Review.Titre: The prices have become sky-high so I'm…
Review.Contenu: The prices have become sky-high so I'm no longer ordering.  But in the past I've had very good experiences.

Review.Titre: Way Overpriced
Review.Contenu: Everyone was very nice however, the pricing for your products is outrageous. The same crab cakes they charge $12 for are about $6 locally.In my book, that’s a rip off.

Review.Titre: Lump Crab
Review.Contenu: I felt that the lump crab had a lot of shells in it. Also very expensive, I picked up a 1lb at a high end market near me and it was roughly half the price.I received as a gift card which was lovely from a friend, but would hesitate to use again

Review.Titre: Good but not great.
Review.Contenu: Website navigation not great.Too many bones in salmon steaks.But the biggy is shipping costs are too high.

Review.Titre: Snow crab not filled.
Review.Contenu: Ordered 2 snow crab clusters 9-11 oz. Only received less than 1 snow crab clusters. Not even a whole order. All other seafood arrived just fine and frozen.

Review.Titre: Not my best shipment
Review.Contenu: Not my best shipment. Cancelled half the order and the oysters I did get were small and just average.

Review.Titre: I order 2 dozen oysters
Review.Contenu: I order 2 dozen oysters, 1/2 east coast and 1/2 west coast.  The east coast were great, but the west coast were terrible, they were not edible

Review.Titre: I thought I would try to make a sashimi…
Review.Contenu: I thought I would try to make a sashimi platter and the fish had a lot of cord in it. Not sure if I used the correct fish or not.

Review.Titre: The order came a day late
Review.Contenu: The order came a day late. Also I got less than 1/2 dozen edible oysters out of 12 I ordered. Otherwise it was great.

Review.Titre: Contents of box was filled with fluid.
Review.Contenu: Contents of box was filled with fluid.Possibly from the bags not holding liquid. So far, so good on the halibut.

Review.Titre: I’m new at ordering
Review.Contenu: I’m new at ordering, so maybe I over looked a detail or two. Very happy with the packaging as the fish was still frozen when it arrived. Wasn’t too thrilled with the salmon in the box as they were all tail sections and very thin. In the future I will look for ~8 oz. thicker portions, if you sell them.

Review.Titre: I have only tried the crab cakes and…
Review.Contenu: I have only tried the crab cakes and unfortunately did not like them at all! I have another box and will not eat them!I have just received my order as I am a first time customer I hope that the rest will be better

Review.Titre: Could have been covid shipping drlays…
Review.Contenu: Could have been covid shipping delays but the product never made in in time twice.  Had the throw it out.  I did get a refund though

Review.Titre: Can no longer afford the price of…
Review.Contenu: Can no longer afford the price of shipping to Florida.  Fish has been always fresh.

Review.Titre: The Colossal shrimp
Review.Contenu: The Colossal shrimp, at $55 per pound arrived shrunken.  I’ve had bigger shrimp in a pint of Chinese food.

Review.Titre: In a packet with 2 pieces one fillet…
Review.Contenu: In a packet with 2 pieces one fillet was fresh and the other not so fresh.

Review.Titre: Well ordered a blue fin tuna kit sucked…
Review.Contenu: Well ordered a blue fin tuna kit sucked paid highest $$$$ for rice no tuna I’ll never order from here again that was a ripp off I guess Covid the excuse I don’t know but never again EVER IT WAS REALLY THAT STUPID OVER $ 100.00 for rice geese I through that crap  away I wish I took a damn picture

Review.Titre: Our Clams and Mussels where open upon…
Review.Contenu: Our Clams and Mussels where open upon arrival but did not smell bad.Everything else was great

Review.Titre: Crab Cakes
Review.Contenu: I didn’t like the crab cakes at all. No pieces of crabmeat all was shredded & no much seasoning

Review.Titre: Ordered 1 lb razor clams but only got 3…
Review.Contenu: Ordered 1 lb razor clams but only got 3 that weighted in at .79 lbs, at $25 lb that is a few bucks. Guess they didn’t want to go over a pound but don’t charge full lb price for an order that was short.  Fish was good, bacon wrapped shrimp were good, and the oysters were acceptable.

Review.Titre: My first and LAST order with F.F.M
Review.Contenu: My first order with F.F.M. #50000160201 was received as scheduled on 11/23/22. All looked great except that there was NO 2lb to 4lb WHOLE RED SNAPPER anywhere to be found. What I DID receive was one blister pack containing 2ea 5oz to 7oz Halibut Fillets along with the Shrimp & Scallops. You enclosed some very nice literature telling the story of F.F.M. and your skilled Fishmongers and the close relationships that you have with your team of Commercial Fishermen who supply you with your fresh Fish & Shellfish. There's even a section about adorning our Holiday Tables with Whole Fish instead of the more traditional Turkey, Ham or Prime Rib Roasts. And I wanted to do that for two family members and I so I ordered the larger size Whole Red Snapper that you offer. Imagine my surprise when I opened the box to find 2lbs of Shrimp, 1lb of Large Dry Scallops and one small pack of Halibut Fillets... with no WHOLE RED SNAPPER anywhere to be found...Am I impressed with my first order from F.F.M..?  Uhh... no I am not. This error forced me to throw the Shrimp, Fish and Scallops into my FREEZER, totally eliminating the reason I ordered FRESH SEAFOOD FROM YOUR SITE and get BACK IN MY TRUCK and DRIVE BACK TO THE GROCERY STORE I HAD JUST LEFT NOT TEN MINUTES BEFORE IN AN ATTEMPT TO GET SOMETHING FOR ME TO COOK FOR THANKSGIVING DINNER... Needless to say, I am not impressed with F.F.M. whatsoever. I WANTED to like your site and it's great Seafood but this actually left me with a Sour taste and poor attitude for the remainder of the day as well as Thanksgiving dinner. What does Fulton Fish Market think I should do for Christmas 🎅 and New Years Eve..? 🥳 I'm thinkin PRIME RIB, HAM OR EVEN A... wait for it... a 🦃..!Anything but Seafood.. 🍤

Review.Titre: Did not realize they were unschucked!
Review.Contenu: Did not realize they were unschucked!!  My mistake I guess.    Do you ever sell schucked??

Review.Titre: Yellowtail Snapper
Review.Contenu: The yellowtail snapper did not taste as good as the red snapper I get at my local fish store.

Review.Titre: I liked everything I received
Review.Contenu: I liked everything I received , but the cuddle fish arrived with the bag opened and freezer burnt

Review.Titre: Other than the interior of the package…
Review.Contenu: Other than the interior of the package being drenched in squid residual liquids and the wrong fish being sent... I have yet to try anything as I threw out the squid and repackaged everything else and placed in freezer.

Review.Titre: Several pkgs of fish were almost completely thawed.
Review.Contenu: The box arrived just a little after it was expected, which wasn't a problem.  I was surprised, however, given my previous extremely good experience with Fulton, that some of the fish had almost completely thawed.  The  ice packs were still hard; perhaps it was the cardboard outerbox that contributed to the problem.  Previous shipments have come in styrofoam containers.

Review.Titre: Fish arrived strong smelling and almost…
Review.Contenu: Fish arrived strong smelling and almost at room temperature. I don’t think I’ll order again. I did prepare the mussels and they were good, only tossed about 6.

Review.Titre: I was unable to try any of the products…
Review.Contenu: I was unable to try any of the products because the weather prevented delivery.

Review.Titre: The items arrived late in the afternoon.
Did not arrived frozen
Review.Contenu: Did not arrived frozen. Was almost room temperature and soft to touch - had to cook it right away. Dissatisfied

Review.Titre: Not what I expected
Review.Contenu: Portion sizes were small and fish thin. For the price we were disappointed.

Review.Titre: Ordered 4 Branzino fish
Review.Contenu: Ordered 4 Branzino fish, 3 were ok 1 was mashed up

Review.Titre: The quality was good not great like I…
Review.Contenu: The quality was good not great like I was hoping for. When you factor in the shipping cost it was not a good value. But overall it was acceptable. I also received an email after I received my order, that my order has shipped and was on the way. This was 2 days after I received my order. Communication is a major flaw here.

Review.Titre: Attention needed.
Review.Contenu: Product is excellent.  Additional ice requested for shipping not provided so product arrived totally thawed.

Review.Titre: The oysters and clams were great
Review.Contenu: The oysters and clams were great.  Only about 1/3 of the muscles opened.

Review.Titre: 50% of oysters were bad
Review.Contenu: Ordered 2 types of oysters.  One package was great, the second package was not. The shells were open and they were very dry inside. Could not eat them, very unpleasant taste and texture.Other items in the order:Mussels were greatTrout were greatFrozen shrimp and scallops were fine

Review.Titre: Defrosted upon delivery
Review.Contenu: While I understand that we are in the summer months, all my frozen products arrived defrosted. I had intended to keep them frozen for future use, and refreezing really impacted the quality. I was disappointed. The fresh product was great and of high quality. In the future I will order only fresh and freeze myself. Good prices and appreciate the quick delivery.

Review.Titre: Oysters were good
Review.Contenu: Oysters were good, having said that of the 36 we purchased 6 were slightly open and had to throw away. Some others were almost without water inside which means old and losing freshness.

Review.Titre: Fish were fresh but half-thawed
Review.Contenu: Fish were fresh but delivered half-thawed despite ordering all frozen items. Was disappointing to have thawedcitems that i meant to stock up in the freezer for a while.

Review.Titre: Unable to track shipment!
Mixed review
Review.Contenu: The salmon was good. Unfortunately, the oysters did not all open up.

Review.Titre: Fish Bones
Review.Contenu: The fish bones I received for my broth were great. Unfortunately 2 of the 4 packages I purchased (not inexpensive either) only had HALF a head each, rather than what is pictured and described online. That was disappointing, as I was specifically making the purchase FOR the heads. Hopefully I’ll have better luck next time?🤷🏼‍♀️

Review.Titre: Stuff almost melted.
Unfrozen Shrimp
Review.Contenu: When we received our package, the frozen shimp was defrosted and had a brownish color.  Since everything else was frozen, it would appear that it shipped that way from your store.I called and sent a picture of the product immediately to your customer service department and they gave me a credit.The product has been fine, but the shipping error gives you a lesser rating.

Review.Titre: The whole Whiting fish looked more like…
Review.Contenu: The whole Whiting fish looked more like a sardine.

Review.Titre: I was not nearly satisfied with 2 tails…
Review.Contenu: I was not nearly satisfied with 2 tails of grouper..(2 tails)...Mussels most definitely not the freshest..Did not smell like ocean..Smelled like they were on last leg....On the other hand impressive packaging..Frederic

Review.Titre: The packaging was strange
Review.Contenu: The packaging was strange. 3 or 4 ice blocks on the bottom with the shrimp on top of the ice blocks followed by the fish cakes and salmon all wrapped in insulated paper. Everything was in a large heavy-duty plastic bag wide open.When I opened the box there was a powerful, but not offensive fish odor. The open plastic bag explained that. The cold from the ice blocks would preserve the contents much better if it was closed tight during the journey.

Review.Titre: Good but frozen items arrived thawed
Review.Contenu: My overall order was good and the freshness of the fish is amazing.However, all my frozen items arrived thawed, which forces me to cook and eat them right away and that wasn't my plan at all... felt like a waste...

Review.Titre: The razor clams i ordered were supposed…
Review.Contenu: The razor clams i ordered were supposed to be 6-8 per pound.  There were definitely more like 20-25 per pound.  They were a pain to clean and the yield was poor.  The clams were very fresh though.  The halibut collars were great.The sockeye salmon was okay.  The flesh was really mushy in some areas.

Review.Titre: Excellent Packaging
Review.Contenu: Excellent Packaging, Delivery, and Customer Services. However, the freshness of shrimp is questionable, though there is no ammonia smelling / tasting, the shrimp texture is so not firm, not as fresh as advertised.Note that shrimps were well packaged and were not thawed when arrived. I couldn’t figure out why it cannot have the same freshness as other shrimps I get from WholeFood

Review.Titre: GREAT customer service, on orig mixed review
Review.Contenu: I got norovirus after eating the oysters on WED 1/5 ... not sure but oysters were tagged 12/21 date of Harvest?  IT's just a possibility of course, cannot be certain, but suspect. However,  the monkfish was excellent.  the mussels were a good price point but little meats inside.  The company was concerned and gave me credit more than I expected, so i will try again, for sure on fish!

Review.Titre: Made things right.Very professional and sending me new order of haddock.Very much appreciated.It was explained to me how this could have happened. Thanks to all and will review again next week.😊
Review.Contenu: Received my first order on Thursday.Was disappointed when salmon was not individually sealed and more disappointed when my haddock was packed in a heap. Two pkgs. several of the haddock pieces were torn up….guile badly. Not nice fillets that you would serve anyone. Good for a chowder. I’ve never given a bad review in my life and this is very disappointing.  Giving the package a 3 star is a stretch but feel the fish is healthy food.😂. Linda Chambers

Review.Titre: We did receive the product in time
Review.Contenu: We did receive the product in time, too much packaging, but the process was wobderful.We were disappointed of the quality, we received two rocks, pine cones in the dirty package of snails. It did not stop us from enjoying the snails but we encountered more work to cleaning and I would suggest they be cleaned. I didnt weigh them but with the excess stuff and sand I'm not umpressed.

Review.Titre: Whole lobster 3lbs.Mostly water…
Review.Contenu: Whole lobster 3lbs.Mostly water ,lacking in meat.Steelheaded Trout very sweet and solid.I’ve been eating whole lobster ,for Fifty years.Previously lived near NYC and Philadelphia.My son-in-law owned a Retail and Wholesale business in Emmaus,Pa.I apologize if you feel this is unfair.I forgot to order a female with roe. Thank You

Review.Titre: I had to toss four of the clams I…
Review.Contenu: I had to toss four of the clams I bought because they were past their sell-by date (they didn't open when cooked). The other items looked fine; no bad smells or anything. But the only item I've cooked so far was the clams and 4 bad ones are too many.

Review.Titre: The e-gift card system could use some help
Review.Contenu: This past Christmas I sent my brother a $100 e-gift card for Fulton Fish Market and he didn't receive it. When I brought it to the attention of the customer service representative, she emailed me the gift card number to forward to my brother so he could use it. Obviously this isn't optimal as I'd hoped he'd have it in his inbox on Christmas but the customer service rep was very nice and helpful on the phone, which I greatly appreciated.

Review.Titre: Little Neck Clams…
Review.Contenu: I had order 3 dozen little Neck Clams and Mussels.  The mussels were great but of the individually packed clams 1 dozen were littlenecks and the other 2 Cherrystone.  It may seem unimportant but for the recipe that I was using they were too large.  Since I am a fisherman and have worked on head boats for years, I do know the difference in the sizes and was disappointed

Review.Titre: Fish good! DELIVERY BAD!!
Review.Contenu: The fish we ordered is great! Although, the delivery service was NOT!!!! They left the box on top of our mailbox. I watch the man just leave it and he did not even ring or knock on our house door. That fish would have not been eatable if I had not seen him delivering the box. We live in Austin Tx and the weather is sunny and in the 70's.

Review.Titre: Order was shipped and delivered promptly
Review.Contenu: Order was shipped and delivered in a timely manner and arrived cold.  The packing of my scallops was not satisfactory.  They were in a plastic container which had broken in shipping.  The container leaked and a couple of scallops were outside the container.  The rest of the shipment was intact and in excellent shape.

Review.Titre: CONFUSED
Review.Contenu: Order received however anchovies (SKU 429-1) $13.99 was not in the package and the total price order of $100.15 was still the same.  I've written to customer service about this; no response yet.  Bring me up to date.  Thank you.#620000078920. The items received were top quality and i'm very pleased with what I received.

Review.Titre: 1-Items were not packaged as requested.
Review.Contenu: 1-Items were not packaged as requested.2- missing items.3-reciepents all said boxes was not packed with thoughtfulness, more like a rush job and boxes was to big for smaller orders. Might of retained cold better.4- frozen items was past defrosted and going in to the warm stage.We all realize it has to be FedEx but..........

Review.Titre: Great service but questionable freshness
Review.Contenu: I ordered fresh seafood (stone crab claws and lump crabmeat) for Christmas dinner.  The shipment came right on time and well packed to maintain cold.  The problem was that the jumbo lump crabmeat was not lump at all and not fresh.  When I called, they removed it from my bill which was nice.  However, it altered my Christmas meal.

Review.Titre: Fulton Christmas Gift
Review.Contenu: I sent my father and his wife a Christmas gift order. My gift card that I included in my order was not included in their order, so they didn’t know who it was from. The mussels had to be steamed open, I thought these were more easily edible. They are in their 80’s and I would have preferred they didn’t have such a hard time with them.

Review.Titre: I ordered for the first time, but.......
Review.Contenu: I ordered for the first time. The size of the fish was smaller than I expected. The most disappointing thing was that the bag containing the squid was not sealed and the liquid inside was leaking from it. And, of the 12 Clams, one had a cracked shell and the contents were black and rotten. After that, I contacted customer service and asked for a refund. I used the coupon this time, so I thought it was good, but I will never buy it without the coupon next time.

Review.Titre: Couple of recommendations:
Review.Contenu: Couple of recommendations:1 - freezer ready packing. We had to eat within 2 days or pack for a freezer. 2 - It's expensive3 - Food was great!4 - Recommendations for Cooking5 - Perhaps some seasonings to come along (small samples)My expectation was that it would come freezer ready due to the price of the food. I didn't expect to have to eat it the same day. Also, I had to google best way to cook it. It'd be great if there was a sample for seasonings as well as a best cooking recommendation to make sure that it comes out great!

Review.Titre: Easy service
Review.Contenu: I would love to give them 5 stars but I can’t. Bottom line is I sent lobsters and oysters down to my parents for a special dinner and was shorted one lobster. They did credit me back the one lobster that was missing. But the moment was ruined. I probably wouldn’t not recommend using this company to friends and family.

Review.Titre: I ordered Sea Bream which was fantastic…
Review.Contenu: I ordered Sea Bream which was fantastic and portions as described. The Branzino was a bit of disappointment, the 2lbs/fish selection was replaced with 2(1lb fish). I have not tried yet but wasn't expecting a replacement without notification.

Review.Titre: Quality very good, contents not all there
Review.Contenu: What I received was very good and the quality was top notch. Customer service was quick to respond when I called and they are fixing the order. This caused an inconvenience for me which is the only reason they don’t get 5 stars. I would order from them in the future as the quality was very good.

Review.Titre: I was excited to try Fulton Fish…
Review.Contenu: I was excited to try Fulton Fish Market.  The fish looked good when arrived but it had already defrosted which makes me a little nervous, but it didn't smell bad so I refroze it and fingers crossed when I go to cook it, that it will still be good.  Haven't actually cooked any yet.

Review.Titre: No notice of cancelled item in order
Review.Contenu: Received my order within 2 days.  Order was packed with dry ice and to my surprise, the ice was still intact with the product frozen solid. Now the issue with this order-one item was absent without any explanation.. no email, no indication in the package.  I had to retrieve my placed order via the web and then notice a credit was given for that item. For that reason I probably won’t order with this company again-not a good customer service.  Have not tried the halibut yet..so no comment at this time.

Review.Titre: Frozen items (Tuna and octopus) were good but clams' and  oysters were not.
Review.Contenu: Frozen items (Tuna and Octopus) were good but clams missing and need info on how to shuck oysters. Customer service staff (Maria) was responsive to complain of missing clams (received only 9 instead of 12.) Corrective action is being addressed.

Review.Titre: Freshness Guaranteed
Review.Contenu: Freshness Guaranteed 12/13/23The order arrived timely in well insulated boxes that guarantee freshness. I’m impressed by the amount of dry ice used to keep it cold. I’m yet to cook any of the fish. Tolu Oluwole

Review.Titre: The fish looks great
Review.Contenu: The fish looks great.  We haven't had it yet; however, it was definitely partially thawed by the time we got it.  I can't imagine ordering fish from you in the summer.

Review.Titre: Overall this was a great experience!
Review.Contenu: Overall this was a great experience.  The only problem was that my order was delayed a day. The package was  securely wrapped and the fish was perfect.

Review.Titre: They care about my satisfaction and…
Review.Contenu: They care about my satisfaction and address any concerns  have.

Review.Titre: The whole process was very good
Review.Contenu: The whole process was very good, the fish excellent, the only wish not fulfilled was not being able to order more than one count monkfish per order.  I asked a sale rep online during the ordering but did not receive a definitive answer so guessing munkfish must be in demand?

Review.Titre: Good not Great
