Review.Contenu: Good, but not excellent, quality products. Tuna fillet was fresh but unevenly filleted & with a significant section of white tissue. Crabmeat was fresh but bland. No complaints at all about packing & delivery.

Review.Titre: Superb Service
Review.Contenu: It is rare to find a company that monitors, responds and remediates customer issues - no one does it better than Fulton. The service actually earns 6 stars, thanks Sarah! I was not pleased with my farmed selections so I’m headed to the “wild”side because they’ve  earned my  respect and another shot at my business.

Review.Titre: Everything has been very good with all…
Review.Contenu: Everything has been very good with all of my many orders Not happy about now having to pay shipping charges

Review.Titre: The fish is gorgeous and perfect size
Review.Contenu: The fish is gorgeous and perfect size.  I would have given 5 stars, but for the packing.  The box was packed perfectly, arrived frozen.  But the dry ice was not sealed in its bag.  It was loosely wrapped without sealing.  I was so excited to get to the fish, I did not read that it was dry ice and since it slid out of its plastic bag, my first instinct was to catch it before it hit the floor.  I hardly suffered for it, just slight burns on my finger tips.  In future, I will wear gloves and hopefully dry ice will be in sealed bag where it cannot drop out of it.

Review.Titre: Great food and great delivery
Review.Contenu: Great food and great delivery.  The only criticism would be that the containers of oysters were smashed because of packing.  Too loose.It is challenging to fix shipping issues.

Review.Titre: Good Selection. Easy to Order.
Review.Contenu: I ordered some frozen salmon as a gift. Process of ordering was easy. Package arrived when expected and, according to my friend, packed very well and safely.My only "ding" and what kept this from being a 5-star experience is that I wanted to order Alaskan salmon, not Atlantic salmon, but Alaskan is restricted to a subscription order and I only needed a one-time purchase.

Review.Titre: Fresh fish tasted great packing needs improvement
Review.Contenu: The fresh white fish tasted fabulous. Packing definitely needs some improvement. All the packages of the frozen lobster and Barramundi were not sealed properly,  allowing all the fish juices and water to leak into the box. The fish and lobster that I ordered  were more than partially defrosted.  Packing should have included some dry ice for the frozen products, with a separation for the fresh.

Review.Titre: Not saying great
Review.Contenu: Not saying great. I would be more comfortable with shellfish if in fact I got it "next day" as FedEx says.All Companies need to understand that FedEx is not the same everywhere, especially in California where one day could turn into two, three, or more.You need to use UPS and/or USPS when sending anything to California.What a strange beast California is!

Review.Titre: Thanks!
Review.Contenu: The shipment arrived overnight as promised; first time in months!  The tuna, salmon and halibut were delicious.  The grouper special not so good;  very hard to grill properly.  Probably not your fault but nonetheless less a disappointing experience.

Review.Titre: Pretty Good
Review.Contenu: The packaging with the ice packs was ample.  The monk fish portions seemed a bit small.  The clams were fine though small too.  The shrimp were good sized though a little fishy.

Review.Titre: Lobster and Clams, Oh, My
Review.Contenu: Our order arrived just as promised. We ordered two dozen little neck clams and every single one opened and was delicious. The lobster tails were very good but not quite as big as the ones we ordered last year. They were a bit disappointing. We'll try again next year. This is our Christmas gift to each other. Thanks.

Review.Titre: The Fulton Fish Market is as great as promised!
Review.Contenu: The Fulton Fish Market was exactly what I hoped it would be…a great place to obtain delicious seafood. Living in central Midwest in a rural town is a major block to obtaining the types of fresh seafood we love to eat. FFM had the choices and shipped it to us at the time arranged. I did not give 5 stars as our shipment was 48 later than anticipated but the customer service was excellent when I called to check on my shipment. My husband was pleasantly surprised with the freshness of the fish and shrimp.

Review.Titre: Delivery and handling was on point
Review.Contenu: Delivery and handling was on point. The scallops were perfectly fantastic. My wife will love the caviar.My one critique would be that I received a spurring email with a discount code, but after shopping, I was unable to use the discount code at checkout because some items in my cart were ineligible for the discount, but others were. So I didn't get the discount on ANY items. This was annoying, but I went ahead with the transaction. I don't have buyer's remorse, but I do have a tiny thorn in my side, over it.

Review.Titre: The fish was excellent!
Review.Contenu: The fish was excellent!  I have to admit I was skeptical when the package first came because there was a definite "fishy" odor but the ice packs were frozen so I gave it a try and the swordfish was excellent.  The reason for 4 and not  5 stars is because for the price the portions were very small.

Review.Titre: Well packaged and arrived on time
Review.Contenu: Well packaged and arrived on time.  Salmon portions were firm and had great flavor.  Personally, I would have preferred each salmon cut to be individually package with its weight provided for easier use and planning.

Review.Titre: Order arrived as promised everything…
Review.Contenu: Order arrived as promised everything was expected. I have ordered soft shell clams before and have had one to three broken shells. This time there were seven.the amazing thing was four of the seven were still alive.eat all seven the same day of receiving the order and the were fine. Thanks

Review.Titre: First Time Order, Very Good
Review.Contenu: My order (salmon and bacon wrapped scallops) arrived in a box packed with dry ice which kept the contents fresh. The arrival date was as promised and I received notification which the order was on its way. The quality of the order was good.  Unfortunately, I am on a fixed income and would not be consistently order from Fulton Fish Market.  I placed this order in conjunction with an Amex promotion.

Review.Titre: First time I ordered and got the “Free…
Review.Contenu: First time I ordered and got the “Free first order up to $75.00”.  Customer service and delivery were great.  The taste of the snow crab legs and shrimp were also great.  The reason I gave four stars was for price.  I realize this was a free order but when I saw how tiny and few the crab legs were I was astonished!  $30 per bag of 6 very small legs ( 7-11ozs.).  I can buy 1 lb. for $11.99 at my local market and they taste just as good.  I appreciate trying your seafood for shipping cost, but way too expensive to order at full price.

Review.Titre: The seafood has always been phenomenal
Review.Contenu: The seafood has always been phenomenal. I buy direct from many places and always find the Fulton Fish Market to be as good or better. Usually 5 star, but last shipment boxing barely held together wit box split and internal packing hanging out...but NO spoilage.

Review.Titre: I ordered several times because my…
Review.Contenu: I ordered several times because my clients vacation home are land locked and it was so convenient to get fresh seafood shipped so quickly. loved that part. So I got the following: pei musselsred snapperlarge lobster tailsshrimpI already submitted a review on the mussels. I do NOT recommend freezing them before use even according to the pamphlet directions. I had to unfortunately needed to freeze because there was  change in my menu so I couldn't use them right away. The red snapper I had 2 shipments. The first had single portion sizes the second had whole filets thus I received more than the first order. Portion sizes varied. I have a picture but I see there is no way to submit it on this review. Everything else was great and delicious.

Review.Titre: Could’ve been 5 star but FF provided a discount coupon for future orders instead of missing product
Review.Contenu: Was able to use a discount, and Sunday holiday box to family out of state. The bacon wrapped shrimp did not contain the full amount of eight pieces. I contacted Fulton and instead of sending out additional shrimp, they provided a coupon for me to use necessitating a future order. So in essence, if I don’t order again in the future I’m just out the product. I would’ve preferred them to make it right for the gift receiver instead of providing a coupon.  The quality has been high and the response time has been quick but I’m not sure I would order in the future going forward.

Review.Titre: Purchase confirmation
Review.Contenu: I made order but did not receive a confirmation email. Eleven days later I received a response email stating that the order was due to be shipped the following day. Order was delivered a day later due to shipping problems. Other than that, product was excellent.

Review.Titre: Product was fresh and packed extremely…
Review.Contenu: Product was fresh and packed extremely well and delivered timely. I ordered oysters, shrimp and steamer clams. There were a few broken steamers and I wish they'd identified what type of oysters were sent, but other than that I was very happy with my order

Review.Titre: The service and delivery were…
Review.Contenu: The service and delivery were excellent.The Manila clams were really good, although several were more the size of little necks, thus the 4/5 stars.The frozen shrimp and frozen branzino are in the freezer for another time.I’ll be a customer again.

Review.Titre: Some problems if new to raw oysters
Review.Contenu: The steamers and salmon roe were as expected - and I enjoyed them both a lot.  I had more problems with my first try at fresh oysters.  I printed out your shucking instructions (I had bought a good shucking knife) to help me.  At first I had little luck,  By the end I finished the last 8 oysters (3 different kinds) in under a half hour and really enjoyed them.  I did have to throw out four I couldn't open - but by the time I finished I felt more confident and may try another dozen in the future.  You provided good instructions for keeping the oysters fresh in the refrigerator for 3 days - great for my 3 dozen oysters.  Thanks so much for recommending I use a towel for opening the oysters!

Review.Titre: No issues with the fish but with the…
Review.Contenu: No issues with the fish but with the delivery. My box was not delivered in front of my door as requested but put in a metal looker which with the heat is not ideal for fish preservation. Would suggest you put perishable stickers so the FedEx delivery people are not aware and follow better instructions. Thanks

Review.Titre: I don’t have any issue with the quality…
Review.Contenu: I don’t have any issue with the quality of the fish , but very upset with FedEx delivery. The shipment was to be delivered before 4 PM . Looks like the FedEx driver went beyond our house for miles and deliver was made past 7 PM . Missed the fishes for Friday dinner !!

Review.Titre: Most of my order was fine but the…
Review.Contenu: Most of my order was fine but the mussels I bought had a lot of dead ones in the bundle.  I was disappointed because I took the Fulton Fish Market at its word.  Finest quality.  The mussels were an important part of my Christmas Eve dinner.

Review.Titre: Very happy with the delivery to North…
Review.Contenu: Very happy with the delivery to North Carolina Charlotte area. All very fresh! I live in an area where we have to depend on poor quality supermarket seafood. I would give 5 stars but the "Colossal" shrimp are far from even extra large. Medium to large at best.

Review.Titre: My order shipped and arrived exactly as…
Review.Contenu: My order shipped and arrived exactly as promised.  The price of the seafood I bought was reasonable.  Would have given the experience 5 stars but was unable to track my package on the "Shop" app.  In fact, couldn't get it to work at all.  Otherwise, everything was fine.

Review.Titre: The trout and bacon wrapped scallops…
Review.Contenu: The trout and bacon wrapped scallops were great!  One of the lobster tails in our order was a bit dicey.  The flesh was a bit mealy and the shell had been cracked.  Overall, a great first experience with Fulton Fish Market.

Review.Titre: Overall great products
Review.Contenu: Overall great products, some.of the best seafood I have ever prepared at home.Package was leaking fish juice and some items almost thawed out, depite ordering them frozen. Wish shipping was free for the cost of the items.

Review.Titre: The food arrived on time and was fresh
Review.Contenu: The food arrived on time and was fresh!  Everything is fine, I just hope that the labels on the food can be changed to plastic in the future, because they are paper labels, so due to humidity, they are all rotten, and I can't tell the specific type of food!  Hope your company can do better and better!

Review.Titre: Everything came on time and what we’ve…
Review.Contenu: Everything came on time and what we’ve eaten so far has been very good. We did find three pea crabs in three out of a dozen Blue Point oysters (that was a shocker! Had never seen or heard of those before), plus one that was missing the oyster from the shell, but from what I read online these are fairly common mishaps and not a fault of Fulton’s.

Review.Titre: packaging
Review.Contenu: It would be nice of the frozen fish were individually wrapped or packaged so they could be cut apart without having to re-wrap them.

Review.Titre: Fluke not fresh enough for cured dish
Review.Contenu: The trout roe was amazing. But we were curing the fluke for a NYE dish, and it just wasn't as fresh as it needed to be for such a dish. It tasted excellent cooked, but the fishiness came through on the cured dish.

Review.Titre: First shipment was excellent
Review.Contenu: First shipment was excellent . All fish was good.Second shipment ( all collars ,for soup and broth), the fresh fish was good The frozen fish ( Halibut collar and cod collar) was old and stinky. I called immediately and received refund credit. Nevertheless I will order again as where I live good fish is difficult to find. Fulton is my only option

Review.Titre: Fish is fresh and delivery was smooth
Review.Contenu: Fish is fresh and delivery was smooth! Main downside is that there's a $150 order minimum for free shipping.  Only other suggestion to increase the Delivery Instruction field so that there's enough space to enter instructions (at least 50 characters).Want to add that customer service was excellent!!

Review.Titre: Everything was good
Review.Contenu: Everything was good, including delivery.

Review.Titre: Very good communication from the Logistics team…
Review.Contenu: Very good communication from the logistics team. Oysters arrived on time despite the blizzard in the NE. Minor issue with some oysters, that I hope Fulton will correct. Overall good experience.

Review.Titre: The 15% off sealed the decision whether…
Review.Contenu: The 15% off sealed the decision whether it was worth the overall cost vs buying local. Plus, the actual wild caught U10 shrimp w/o sodium additives

Review.Titre: First purchase
Review.Contenu: I made my first purchase form a email i got showing a 2 for the price of one item ,, but when the package was delivered on time and in good condition , i did not receive the extra items ,, im still happy with what i ordered and will do more business in the future

Review.Titre: The delivery was great and seafood awesome
Review.Contenu: The delivery was great. I requested an earlier day and you were able to help. Very fresh. One muddy Wellfleet and 4 dead mussels.  But otherwise excellent and fresh. Good time will do it again.

Review.Titre: Outstanding taste and very fresh
Review.Contenu: The freshness and the taste were outstanding. I will order again.The packaging was questionable when we received it. One of the bags was open that held the lobster tails and holes in a couple of bags holding the fish. If there could be some quality control on the packaging, I would have given 5 stars.

Review.Titre: Delicious
Review.Contenu: My only criticism is that the two pieces of halibut were very different thicknesses and so would cook differently. I cut the thicker one in half and made them the same size. They were delicious and very fresh.

Review.Titre: Lobster and caviar
Review.Contenu: Out of the 2lb lobster but replaced with two smaller and a credit. Thank you. A little disappointed with the caviar “best buy” date two days prior to the delivery. It was till ok.

Review.Titre: I ordered 4 dozen blue points and 2 lbs…
Review.Contenu: •••edit after 1 day of writing this review, Fulton refunded me for the muscles!! I didn’t even request a refund. I have never received such outstanding customer service from any vendor before. This company is top notch and I will continue to use them for all my seafood needs! I ordered 4 dozen blue points and 2 lbs of green lip muscles. The oysters were absolute heaven! They were extremely fresh, popped just right when opening, and were sweet and briny. Texture was perfect and I will definitely be ordering all my oysters from Fulton from now on! The muscles in the other hand were not up to my satisfaction and had I known how to tell them about my experience other than them asking me to leave a review I would have definitely done that first. Quite a few of the muscles arrived dead. I expect a few to dead loss but this was many more than expected. The ones we were able to stem were sweet and delicious. I would definitely recommend Fulton for all your oyster needs!!!

Review.Titre: I ordered four dozen Littleneck clams…
Review.Contenu: I ordered four dozen Littleneck clams to be delivered to my home in Albuquerque New Mexico.  They arrived within two days. The packaging was excellent and the clams were in fine condition, no cracked shells.  I have eaten the clams raw, in white sauce and in red sauce.  The quality and freshness of the clams were outstanding.  I have one suggestion.  These clams are very fresh and they can be difficult to shuck even for a person who grew up in Queens.  If you watch the Fulton instructional video on shucking clams you will see what I mean.  After some experimentation I found that difficult clams can be relaxed by thirty to forty seconds in the microwave.  The result is a slightly warm  raw clam but all the delicious flavor is still there. Finally I want to thank Nicki Stagg of the customer service office for her outstanding support in answering my concerns.  I will be ordering more items from Fulton Fish Market in the future
